The paper discusses the use of identifiers in ontology development, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also touches on issues related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and software engineering (cs.SE) in terms of usability and implementation. Finally, the paper presents alternatives to the current practice of using monotonically increasing numbers, which is a topic related to programming languages (cs.PL).
